{
  "doc_id": "18191",
  "text": "According to De [CITATION_1] , cluster firms are characterised by a high degree of specialisation and complementarity. The benefits of clustering are very important in connection with innovations, technological changes, and the amount of spending on research and development [CITATION_2] . [CITATION_3] notes that competition among cluster firms forces firms to increasingly innovate, improve, and create new technologies. According to [CITATION_4] , clusters support the firms' productivity and innovation capabilities because these groups of firms have an information database that they can fully use.",
